Important Days of DPRK Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 3 (KCNA) -- A seminar was held in Russia and a lecture and photo exhibition took place in Guinea respectively on Dec. 23 and 24 last year to mark the 15th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 89th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk.
 On display in the venues of the functions were photos showing the immortal exploits of the three generals of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mikhail Panchenko, chairman of the Russian Youth Association for the Study of the Songun Policy, in a report at the seminar highly praised the undying feats of Kim Jong Suk, a great woman revolutionary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The seminar discussed and decided on the issue of significantly organizing a scientific symposium on the Juche idea on the occasion of the Day of the Sun and February 16 in 2007. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Malik Souma, director general of the Kim Il Sung Institute of Agricultural Science in Guinea, gave lectures entitled "Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il holding high the treasured sword of Songun" and "Kim Jong Suk recorded a brilliant page in the history of modern Korea." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message of greetings to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the seminar held in Russia.

Friday Meeting against U.S. and War Held in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 3 (KCNA) -- A Friday meeting for a general view of anti-U.S. and anti-war actions in 2006 was reportedly held near the U.S. embassy in Seoul on Dec. 29 last year under the sponsorship of the Solidarity Meeting for Opposing the U.S. and War and for the Withdrawal of the U.S. Troops in south Korea.
 Speakers at the meeting said that the U.S. committed an unbroken chain of big accidents and steadily increased the funds for the upkeep of the U.S. forces in south Korea in 2006. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that in addition to this the U.S. persistently escalated sanctions and the moves for a war of aggression against the DPRK, they called for raising the voices opposing the U.S. and war and demanding the pullback of the U.S. forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A resolution read out at the meeting called for driving the U.S. troops, a source of war, out of this land and achieving peace without fail in 2007.

Main Trend toward Independence Cannot Be Blocked: Rodong Sinmun 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 3 (KCNA) -- The joint New Year editorial declares that nothing can stop the struggle of the people for independence, notes Rodong Sinmun Wednesday in a signed article, adding: This is an entirely just idea reflecting the invariable aspiration and gigantic strength of the popular masses and the development of the present situation. 
 Noting that an increasing number of people demand independence and a great many countries are following the road of independence, the author of the article goes on:
 The main target of attack in the struggle of the people for independence is imperialism. The cause of independence of the popular masses has run into mounting troubles due to the blatant challenge of the imperialist forces. The prevailing situation calls for a more dauntless struggle against imperialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The present era is an exciting era of Songun. It is an era in which the destiny of the country and the nation and the destiny of the cause of independence of the popular masses mainly depend upon the military might, the might of arms, an era in which the danger of war is averted and a durable peace is achieved with arms. This era of Songun is a new, higher stage in the accomplishment of the human cause of independence. 
 The victory in the struggle for independence lies in unity. Unity based on independence is the source of invincibility and the key to victory. The idea of independence is sure to be brought to victory by the struggle of the united people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Socialism is the ideal and future of humankind. Only socialism can guarantee the realization of the independence of the popular masses and the building of an independent, peaceful and friendly new world. The aspiration of humankind for independence and socialism and the orientation of the development of history toward them never change. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Inexhaustible is the strength of the people desirous of independence and, accordingly, no force on earth can block their struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The struggle of the people for independence will gather strength and develop as the days go by and the imperialist and dominationist forces are fated to suffer destruction. 
 The Workers' Party of Korea and the people of the DPRK this year, too, will positively contribute to the victorious advance of the cause of independence and the cause of socialism of the popular masses under the uplifted banner of independence.
